  <subsection xml:id="summary-factoring-quadratics">
    <title>Summary of Factoring <m>ax^2 + bx + c</m></title>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          (If necessary) Factor out common factors (the GCF).
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p>
                If the leading coefficient is negative, factor out <m>-1</m> from all terms.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p>
                If <m>a = 1</m> (<m>x^2 + bx + c</m>), find two numbers that multiply to <m>c</m> and add to <m>b</m>.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                If <m>a \neq 1</m> (<m>ax^2 + bx + c</m>), use the cross method.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          To check your answer, you can expand (FOIL) and check if you get back the original expression.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </subsection>
